data.enText: one of the things from which sth is made, especially one of the foods that are used together to make a particular dish

data.chText: 椰子是多种咖喱菜的基本成分。
data.enText: Coconut is a basic ingredient for many curries.

data.chText: 我们的护肤霜只含天然成分。
data.enText: Our skin cream contains only natural ingredients.
one of the things or qualities that are necessary to make sth successful

data.chText: 这部作品具有构成一个好的神秘故事所有的因素。
data.enText: It has all the ingredients of a good mystery story.

ex.chText: 他们是该组织中的先进分子。
ex.enText: They are advanced elements in the organization.

ex.chText: 速度是这一体育项目的要素。
ex.enText: Speed is an important element of the athletic event.

synonyms.bx: 尤指一整套系统、计划、作品等中最基本或最重要的成分或特征。

ex.enText: There are many components to the machine.

ex.chText: 该系统由各种部件组成。
ex.enText: This system consists of various components.

synonyms.bx: 指一个整体的组成部分，多用于机器、机械系统等。

ex.chText: 这种护肤霜只含天然成分。
ex.enText: This skin cream contains only natural ingredients.

ex.chText: 面粉和糖是烤面包最重要的原料。
ex.enText: Flour and sugar are the most important ingredients in baking bread.

synonyms.bx: 指混合物的成分，尤指烹饪原料。

tr: a component of a mixture or compound

example: jealousy was a component of his character
two constituents of a musical composition are melody and harmony
the grammatical elements of a sentence
a key factor in her success
humor: an effective ingredient of a speech

tr: food that is a component of a mixture in cooking
example: the recipe lists all the fixings for a salad

value.def: Ingredients are the things that are used to make something, especially all the different foods you use when you are cooking a particular dish.
An ingredient of a situation is one of the essential parts of it.

example.ex: The meeting had all the ingredients of high political drama...
example.tran: 这次会议具备了作为高度戏剧性的政治事件的一切要素。

example.ex: I think that is one of the major ingredients in his success.
example.tran: 我认为那是他成功的主要因素之一。

trans: 食品成分；食品配料；食品配料成分；食品添加剂；食物成分
